  "body": "### description\r\n\r\nUse of `yaml.load` is generally discouraged as it allows execution of arbitrary code from a crafted config.\r\n\r\nWhere its actually necessary to activate these yaml features the load function  should be called with a `Loader` argument\r\n\r\nThere are 2 cases in the source code where the `yaml.load` is used - one is called with the `Loader` arg the other not - eliciting warnings.\r\n\r\n```\r\n/home/envoydev/.cache/bazel/_bazel_envoydev/643fc116b156fc214644eaa6b8d6b57b/sandbox/processwrapper-sandbox/455/execroot/envoy/bazel-out/k8-opt-exec-2B5CBBC6/bin/tools/protodoc/protodoc.runfiles/envoy/tools/protodoc/protodoc.py:592: YAMLLoadWarning: calling yaml.load() without Loader=... is deprecated, as the default Loader is unsafe. Please read https://msg.pyyaml.org/load for full details.\r\n```\r\nin the case where `load` is called with `FullLoader` its not clear to me whether this is actually required or `safe_load` would suffice  - but it *does* avoid the code execution issue\r\n\r\n### references\r\n\r\nhttps://msg.pyyaml.org/load\r\n\r\nhttps://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html\r\n\r\n",
